x4freetext: -STUDY OF DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTIONS OF THE
REACTIONS (N,P) AND (N,A) ON F-19, SI-29, S-32
AND CA-40 AT 5.85 MEV-. IN FRENCH.
DEUTERIUM TARGET. THE NEUTRON SPECTRUM HAD A HALF
THE COUNTER TELESCOPE COMPRISED FOUR SECTIONS
THREE CO2 GAS PROPORTIONEL COUNTERS AND
.ALL FOUR DETECTORS WERE OPERATED IN COINCIDENCE.
.TOTAL CROSS SECTIONS ARE OBTAINED BY SUMMING OVER
BEYOND 165 DEG CONTINUED THE LAST VALUE.
.THE NEUTRON ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION FROM THE INCIDENT
BEAM AND NEUTRON ABSORPTION IN THE TARGET ARE
UNCERTAINTIES REPRESENT THE SUBTENDED SOLID ANGLE.
